<div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; text-align: center">
<font color="#000000"><span style="font-family: georgia; font-size: 24px">
<b><u>Our Mission:</u></b></span>
<span style="font-family: georgia; font-size: 20px;"> 
The BRICK lives Christ’s message to compassionately love and respect those in need.
<span style="font-family: georgia; font-size: 24px">
<b><u>Our Vision:</u></b></span>
<span style="font-family: georgia; font-size: 20px;"> 
To provide services and build relationships to change people’s circumstances and lives through Christ.</span>
<span style="font-family:georgia; font-size: 20px;">
The BRICK Ministries is a partnered effort  between its member churches, businesses, and residents who share the mission and vision of compassionately helping people in need, serving residents of Ashland and Bayfield Counties. The BRICK offers a Food Shelf  Program that distributes food and personal care items at four locations: Ashland, Cable, Cornucopia, and Mellen. The BRICK’s  Benevolence Program assists with emergency financial resources and provides referrals.

The BRICK's Board of Directors and staff are very thankful for the many businesses and volunteers who have offered time and resources to this project. We welcome new  <a title="Volunteers" href="http://thebrickministries.com/?page_id=93">volunteers</a>; we encourage you to come and help serve the community, helping us open the doors to what God wants to provide.

If you would like to <a title="Donate" href="http://thebrickministries.com/donate/financial-donations/">make a tax-free donation</a> to this project,  it would be appreciated and put to good use.

You are welcome to stop by and visit us at 420 Ellis Avenue in Ashland, WI (across from Super One), 9:00 am to 3:30 pm, Monday--Wednesday, 9 am to 7 pm on Thursday.  The BRICK is closed on Fridays.</span></div>
